    "In this section, we introduce our design choices for the final reward signal and techniques to prevent reward hacking issues observed in the early stage of experiments.",
    "Formally, for each prompt-response-rubric pair (q, o, r = {r i } d i=1), the rubric verifier",
    ", where v i is the binary rubric-specific label indicating whether the response o satisfies the user prompt q on rubric r i.",
    "In this paper, we use the most straightforward reward R(q, o, r) = I [V (q, o, r) = 1] as the final reward for rubric-based RL for its simplicity and effectiveness, and provide a preliminary ablation study in Section 5.4.",
    "We leave other reward computation methods (for instance, weighted sum of v i) for future work."
